As a final exercise to VIII.1 in Algebra: Chapter $0$ , we are asked to prove If $\mathcal{F}\colon\operatorname{R-Mod}\to\operatorname{S-Mod}$ is a right-adjoint functor, then $\mathcal{F}$ is left-exact. I am having some trouble proving this. If my overall strategy is right, then one necessary step is to show \begin{equation}
\mathcal{F}(0)=0,
\end{equation} where $0$ is the zero module. However I do not know how to do this. Can someone give a hint? Thanks!
